  else if (text === '!research release') await handleHoldCommand(message, false);
  else if (text === '!research status')  await handleStatusCommand(message);
});
```

`handleHoldCommand(message, activate)`:
- Calls `researchGate.setHold(activate)`
- Replies: `"Research processing paused. Use !research release to resume."` / `"Research processing resumed."`
- No-ops with a message if already in the requested state

`handleStatusCommand(message)`:
- Reports: hold active/inactive, gate reason (if any), pending item count

`require('./research-gate')` is done **inside** these handlers (lazy) to avoid load-order issues since `discord-bot` is required early in the chain.

**Updated exports:**
